rocks.bastion.core

Interface Response

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ModelResponse, RawResponse

    public interface Response
    Defines an HTTP response object containing a status code and associated status text. The response object also contains the HTTP response headers returned by the server. If one of the headers is the Content-type header, the content-type header is available by using the getContentType() method.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Gets the response's body, ready for reading.

    • Method Detail

      • getContentType

        Optional<org.apache.http.entity.ContentType> getContentType()
        Gets the value of the Content-type header that was returned by the server. This same value is also available as part of the headers returned by the getHeaders() methods.
        Returns:
        The value of the Content-type header in this HTTP response. If there's no Content-type header, an empty Optional is returned.

      • getStatusCode

        int getStatusCode()
        Gets the HTTP status code in this response. This is an integer value as described on this page.
        Returns:
        The HTTP status code

      • getStatusText

        String getStatusText()
        The text description of the HTTP status code returned by getStatusCode().
        Returns:
        The HTTP status text

      • getHeaders

        Collection<ApiHeader> getHeaders()
        Returns the collection of HTTP header key-value pairs in this response. This method will always return a non-null collection which could possibly be empty if no headers were returned by the server.
        Returns:
        The collection of HTTP headers

      • getBody

        InputStream getBody()
        Gets the response's body, ready for reading. The input stream returned by this method will always be positioned at the start of the response body and each different invocation of this method will return a new, independent instance of the body input stream.
        Returns:
        The body content sent by the remote end during this HTTP call
